# Solicitation Summary Report: 36C26224Q1523_1

---

## 1. Key Dates
- **Questions Due:** November 6, 2025, 8:00 AM MT (katharine.robert@va.gov)
- **Quotes Due:** November 17, 2025, 9:00 AM MT (No late submissions considered)
- **Full Mobilization/Start Date:** January 1, 2026
- **Period of Performance:** Base year + 4 option years (through December 31, 2030)

---

## 2. Requirement Overview
- **Title:** V212--IDC Wheelchair and Hired Car Service with Ad Hoc Medical Companion (San Diego)
- **Scope:** 24/7 non-emergency wheelchair and hired car transportation for veterans, possibly with medical companion; must cover ambulatory/non-ambulatory/blind/amputee/special needs passengers.
- **Volume:** 1,800–2,100 monthly trips (including after-hours)
- **System:** Must use VetRide scheduling system (VA access/training provided post-award)

---

## 3. Locations
- **Primary:** San Diego VA Medical Center, 3350 La Jolla Village Dr, San Diego, CA 92161
- **Additional:** Community-Based Outpatient Clinics, affiliated clinics; counties: San Diego, Riverside, Imperial, Orange (CA)
- **Possible Extended Area:** Los Angeles (VA Greater LA Healthcare System)

---

## 4. Insurance & Compliance Requirements
- **Vehicle/Workers Comp Insurance:** Must meet VAAR 852.228-71, FAR 28.307-2, and FAR 52.228-5; proof required in submission
- **Licenses:** All local/county/state NEMT/for-hire licenses/proofs required
- **Labor:** Drivers subject to Wage Determination WD 2015-5653 Rev. 28
- **Background Checks:** Special Agreement Check (SAC) required for drivers
- **Invoice:** Must be submitted monthly via electronic means (per VA instructions)

---

## 5. Submission Instructions
- **Eligibility:** 100% SDVOSB set-aside; SDVOSB certification mandatory
- **Submission Format:** Email only; no zip files or hyperlinks; no paper/fax submissions
- **Mandatory Documents:**
  - SF 1449 + all amendments (SF 30)
  - Provided Price/Cost Schedule (Section B.3)
  - Performance Work Statement (PWS)
  - VAAR form Limitation on Subcontracting certificate
  - Insurance documents
  - Management plan (Past Performance Narrative, 2-5 similar contracts)
  - VA Form 10091 (EFT registration)
- **Compliance:** All documents required—partial submissions not considered

---

## 6. Contacts
- **Contract Specialist:** Katharine Robert (katharine.robert@va.gov)
- **Contracting Officer for Protests:** Helena Roba (helena.roba@va.gov)

---

## 7. Evaluation & Award Details
- **Type:** Single-award IDIQ; not multiple awards
- **Method:** Best Value, not LPTA
- **No anticipated discussions; options evaluated in award

---

## 8. Important Considerations
- **VetRide System:** Use/training mandatory; proficiency required post-award
- **Amendment Acknowledgment:** Must acknowledge/sign all amendments
- **Predecessor Contract:** 36C26225P1246 (no prior pricing shared unless publicly available)
- All details and future amendments will be published on SAM.gov.

---

**Summary:**
If qualified (SDVOSB, properly licensed/insured, able to meet high service volume, and can work in San Diego region), this solicitation is a solid opportunity. Attention to submission completeness and compliance is CRITICAL.